---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---
<BaseLayout
  title="Trainers"
  description="Three coaches, forty years of operator memory between them. Meet Jeffrey, Ryan and Chia Wei — the team behind every JF class."
  activeNav="trainers"
  bodyLabel="03 Trainers">

<!-- HERO — full-bleed action photo with centred overlay copy -->
<section class="trainers-hero">
  <div class="trainers-hero-bg">
    <img src="/assets/jfsd-atmos1.jpg" alt="Ryan and Jeffrey running a live training workshop" />
  </div>
  <div class="wrap trainers-hero-overlay">
    <div class="crumb">
      <span>JF SELF DEFENSE</span><span class="sep">/</span><span class="here">TRAINERS</span>
    </div>
    <h1 class="display h1 trainers-hero-h1">
      Three operators.<br/>
      Forty years of work,<br/>
      <span class="red">between us</span>.
    </h1>
    <p class="lede trainers-hero-lede">
      Every class runs the same five-step hierarchy. What changes is the voice,
      the drill, and the body in front of the student.
    </p>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- ==================== PROFILE 01 · JEFFREY ==================== -->
<section class="profile profile-l">
  <div class="wrap profile-card">

    <header class="profile-head">
      <h2 class="profile-name">Jeffrey Fleury</h2>
      <figure class="profile-portrait">
        <div class="img">
          <img src="/assets/jeffrey-square.jpg" alt="Jeffrey Fleury at the heavy bag" />
        </div>
      </figure>
      <div class="profile-head-meta">
        <span class="eyebrow"><span class="dot"></span>FOUNDER · MASTER TRAINER</span>
        <p class="profile-tenure">1991 — present · Singapore</p>
        <p class="profile-subtitle">"When you have to fight, <span class="red">fight to win</span>."</p>
      </div>
    </header>

    <div class="profile-body">
      <article class="profile-prose">
        <p>
          Jeffrey Fleury has been in the security industry for more than <strong>33
          years</strong>, of which <strong>11 years were with the Singapore Police
          Force</strong>. He received the prestigious <em>Long Service and Good
          Conduct Medal</em> when he left.
        </p>
        <p>
          He holds a <strong>specialised security science degree</strong> apart from
          other international security accreditations. He is an <strong>International
          Crime Prevention Specialist (ICPS)</strong> and a <strong>Certified Supply
          Chain Security Specialist (CSCSS)</strong>. He has served as the
          <strong>Country and Regional Security Manager</strong> for established
          multinational companies for <strong>over 22 years</strong>, with security
          coverage and responsibilities spanning the Asia Pacific region — including
          Japan and Australia.
        </p>
        <p>
          With regards to martial arts and other forms of combat training, Jeffrey
          has been involved with the arts for <strong>about 30 years</strong>. He
          holds <strong>black belts in Hapkido and Hanmudo</strong> and is versed in
          various other forms of martial arts and self-defense techniques. In 2018,
          he trained with knife combat expert <strong>Jim Wagner in Vancouver,
          Canada</strong>, and obtained his certification as a <strong>Knife Survival
          Expert Instructor</strong>.
        </p>
        <p>
          What makes JF Self Defense different from other martial arts schools is
          what Jeffrey brings into the room — three decades of operator field
          experience, not just mat hours. The same situational reads that worked on
          the street, on protective details, in convoy and crowd management, become
          the curriculum. Civilians walk out with the same decision tools an
          operator uses, scaled to the situations they actually face.
        </p>
        <p>
          The self-defense techniques he teaches are simple, direct and applicable.
          He believes that if you have to use physical self-defense you are already
          in damage-control mode. The best self-defense is improved self-awareness
          — not putting yourself in harm's way in the first place, so you are less
          likely to be selected as a target. The next best is to avoid the fight
          when one materialises. When neither avenue is left, you need to know how
          to <em>fight to win</em>.
        </p>
        <p class="profile-prose-philosophy">
          That is why his workshops emphasise the soft skills first — posturing,
          communications, distance management — to prevent escalation into the
          physical stage whenever possible. Jeffrey has conducted programmes for
          multinational companies, schools, banks, aesthetic clinics and legal
          firms, in addition to the ongoing self-defence classes run from the JF
          studio in Paya Lebar. Most students arrive looking for technique.
          They leave with judgment.
        </p>
      </article>

      <div class="profile-creds-col">
        <aside class="profile-creds">
          <h3 class="profile-creds-h">Security &amp; protective services</h3>
          <ul class="trainer-creds-list">
            <li><span class="trainer-creds-year">33+ yrs</span><span class="trainer-creds-text">Total security industry experience</span></li>
            <li><span class="trainer-creds-year">22+ yrs</span><span class="trainer-creds-text">Country &amp; Regional Security Manager · APAC, Japan, Australia</span></li>
            <li><span class="trainer-creds-year">11 yrs</span><span class="trainer-creds-text">Singapore Police Force &nbsp;·&nbsp; Long Service &amp; Good Conduct Medal</span></li>
            <li><span class="trainer-creds-year">ICPS</span><span class="trainer-creds-text">International Crime Prevention Specialist</span></li>
            <li><span class="trainer-creds-year">CSCSS</span><span class="trainer-creds-text">Certified Supply Chain Security Specialist</span></li>
            <li><span class="trainer-creds-year">BSc</span><span class="trainer-creds-text">Specialised Security Science degree</span></li>
          </ul>
        </aside>

        <aside class="profile-creds">
          <h3 class="profile-creds-h">Martial arts &amp; combat training</h3>
          <ul class="trainer-creds-list">
            <li><span class="trainer-creds-year">30+ yrs</span><span class="trainer-creds-text">Combined martial arts &amp; combat training</span></li>
            <li><span class="trainer-creds-year">2018</span><span class="trainer-creds-text">Knife Survival Expert Instructor <em>· Jim Wagner, Vancouver</em></span></li>
            <li><span class="trainer-creds-year">Dan</span><span class="trainer-creds-text">Hapkido — Black Belt &nbsp;·&nbsp; Hanmudo — Black Belt</span></li>
            <li><span class="trainer-creds-year">—</span><span class="trainer-creds-text">Versed in various other martial arts &amp; self-defence techniques</span></li>
          </ul>
        </aside>

        <figure class="profile-inset profile-inset-portrait">
          <img src="/assets/jeffrey-range.jpg" alt="Jeffrey Fleury at the pistol range" />
          <figcaption>
            <span>JEFFREY FLEURY · LIVE-FIRE RANGE</span>
            <span>PROTECTIVE SERVICES TRAINING</span>
          </figcaption>
        </figure>
      </div>
    </div>

  </div>
</section>

<!-- BAND 02 — father and son -->
<div class="band band-tight">
  <div class="wrap"><span>FATHER. SON. &nbsp;TWENTY YEARS ON THE SAME MAT.</span></div>
</div>

<!-- ==================== PROFILE 02 · RYAN ==================== -->
<section class="profile profile-r">
  <div class="wrap profile-card">

    <header class="profile-head">
      <h2 class="profile-name">Ryan Fleury</h2>
      <figure class="profile-portrait">
        <div class="img">
          <img src="/assets/ryan.jpg" alt="Ryan Fleury coaching with focus mitts" />
        </div>
      </figure>
      <div class="profile-head-meta">
        <span class="eyebrow"><span class="dot"></span>CO-INSTRUCTOR · CONDITIONING LEAD</span>
        <p class="profile-tenure">Co-founder, JF system · Founder, RF Transformation</p>
        <p class="profile-subtitle">"Transform. Educate. <span class="red">Empower</span>."</p>
      </div>
    </header>

    <div class="profile-body">
      <article class="profile-prose">
        <p>
          Ryan trains clients from all walks of life — university students,
          stay-home mothers, working professionals, CEOs. The people who walk into
          RF Transformation Academy or onto the JF mat aren't athletes with two
          free hours a day. They are people with offices, commutes, mortgages, kids.
          Ryan's job is to design the work to fit the life around it, not the other
          way around — short sessions, honest programming, nutrition that survives a
          takeaway lunch.
        </p>
        <p>
          He grew up inside the system his father built. He has been on the mat
          since he could walk a straight line, served a combat-role national service
          in the Army and Air Force, and earned his BSc in Sport &amp; Exercise
          Sciences. Outside the JF curriculum he founded RF Transformation Academy
          — a holistic system for sustainable body transformation covering strength,
          mobility, recovery, and nutrition (he is a Certified Nutritional Therapist,
          HSA Level 5). He has been featured on Bidvine UK as a top personal trainer.
        </p>
        <p>
          On the JF mat Ryan runs the conditioning and movement tracks — the
          foundations every other technique sits on top of. Footwork, breath
          control, the burst-and-escape principle, the strikes that still work when
          the heart rate is at 180. Where Jeffrey teaches you to read the situation,
          Ryan trains the body that can act on the read.
        </p>

        <figure class="profile-inset">
          <img src="/assets/ryan-coaching.jpg" alt="Ryan Fleury coaching pad work outdoors" />
          <figcaption>
            <span>RYAN FLEURY · PAD WORK</span>
            <span>OUTDOOR SESSION</span>
          </figcaption>
        </figure>
      </article>

      <div class="profile-creds-col">
        <aside class="profile-creds">
          <h3 class="profile-creds-h">Overall experience</h3>
          <ul class="trainer-creds-list">
            <li><span class="trainer-creds-year">Founder</span><span class="trainer-creds-text">RF Transformation Academy <em>· holistic body transformation system</em></span></li>
            <li><span class="trainer-creds-year">Co-fdr</span><span class="trainer-creds-text">JF Self Defense system <em>· simple &amp; effective for civilians</em></span></li>
            <li><span class="trainer-creds-year">8+ yrs</span><span class="trainer-creds-text">Coaching personal, group &amp; corporate clients</span></li>
            <li><span class="trainer-creds-year">16+ yrs</span><span class="trainer-creds-text">Martial arts &amp; combat training</span></li>
            <li><span class="trainer-creds-year">2 yrs</span><span class="trainer-creds-text">Military service · Army &amp; Air Force combat role</span></li>
            <li><span class="trainer-creds-year">UK</span><span class="trainer-creds-text">Featured on Bidvine <em>· Top Personal Trainer &amp; Success Story</em></span></li>
          </ul>
        </aside>

        <aside class="profile-creds">
          <h3 class="profile-creds-h">Education &amp; certifications</h3>
          <ul class="trainer-creds-list">
            <li><span class="trainer-creds-year">BSc</span><span class="trainer-creds-text">Sport &amp; Exercise Sciences</span></li>
            <li><span class="trainer-creds-year">Dip.</span><span class="trainer-creds-text">Sport &amp; Exercise Sciences</span></li>
            <li><span class="trainer-creds-year">L5</span><span class="trainer-creds-text">Certified Nutritional Therapist · HSA</span></li>
            <li><span class="trainer-creds-year">OTC</span><span class="trainer-creds-text">Certified Online Trainer</span></li>
            <li><span class="trainer-creds-year">ISPA</span><span class="trainer-creds-text">Certified in Exercise &amp; Fitness</span></li>
          </ul>
        </aside>

        <aside class="profile-creds">
          <h3 class="profile-creds-h">Martial arts &amp; self-defence</h3>
          <ul class="trainer-creds-list">
            <li><span class="trainer-creds-year">6+ yrs</span><span class="trainer-creds-text">Coaching self-defence, MMA &amp; kickboxing</span></li>
            <li><span class="trainer-creds-year">Dip.</span><span class="trainer-creds-text">Korean self-defence</span></li>
            <li><span class="trainer-creds-year">1st Dan</span><span class="trainer-creds-text">Hanmudo — Black Belt</span></li>
            <li><span class="trainer-creds-year">1st Dan</span><span class="trainer-creds-text">Hapkido — Black Belt</span></li>
            <li><span class="trainer-creds-year">—</span><span class="trainer-creds-text">TKD · BJJ · Krav Maga · Boxing · Judo · Aikido</span></li>
          </ul>
        </aside>
      </div>
    </div>

  </div>
</section>

<!-- BAND 03 — the student joins -->
<div class="band">
  <div class="wrap"><span>FORTY YEARS OF OPERATOR MEMORY. &nbsp;THEN THE STUDENT JOINS THEM.</span></div>
</div>

<!-- ==================== PROFILE 03 · CHIA WEI ==================== -->
<section class="profile profile-c">
  <div class="wrap profile-card">

    <header class="profile-head">
      <h2 class="profile-name">Chia Wei Goh</h2>
      <figure class="profile-portrait">
        <div class="img portrait-placeholder">
          <span class="portrait-placeholder-label">[ PORTRAIT &middot; Chia Wei Goh<br/>to be supplied ]</span>
        </div>
      </figure>
      <div class="profile-head-meta">
        <span class="eyebrow"><span class="dot"></span>ASSISTANT COACH</span>
        <p class="profile-tenure">Ten years a student. One year a coach.</p>
        <p class="profile-subtitle">"The decision tree, <span class="red">above all of it</span>."</p>
      </div>
    </header>

    <div class="profile-body">
      <article class="profile-prose">
        <p>
          Chia Wei walked through the door as a Muay Thai and Aikido practitioner ten
          years ago, looking for the missing piece between those two systems. He
          found it in Jeffrey's curriculum: the layer above technique, the decision
          tree that comes before the strike.
        </p>
        <p>
          Today he runs warm-up rotations, assists with drills, and helps newer
          students through the first weeks of orientation — the period where the
          distance between "I don't understand any of this" and "this is the only
          sensible way to teach it" is shortest if you have a coach who remembers
          being there.
        </p>
      </article>

      <aside class="profile-creds">
        <h3 class="profile-creds-h">Background</h3>
        <ul class="trainer-creds-list">
          <li><span class="trainer-creds-year">2024</span><span class="trainer-creds-text">Joined · JF Self Defense coaching team</span></li>
          <li><span class="trainer-creds-year">2014</span><span class="trainer-creds-text">First class with Jeffrey — still on the mat</span></li>
          <li><span class="trainer-creds-year">—</span><span class="trainer-creds-text">Muay Thai &nbsp;·&nbsp; Aikido</span></li>
        </ul>
      </aside>
    </div>

  </div>
</section>

<!-- EPILOGUE -->
<section class="trainers-epilogue">
  <div class="wrap">
    <p class="epilogue-line">
      <em>The same system, in three voices.<br/>
      The most experienced operator in the room<br/>
      will always be Jeffrey. The doors are open anyway.</em>
    </p>
    <div class="epilogue-rule"></div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- CONTACT — inline form, page-bottom -->
<section class="contact-section" id="book">
  <div class="wrap">
    <div class="contact-inner">
      <div class="contact-pitch">
        <span class="eyebrow"><span class="dot"></span>BOOK A FREE TRIAL</span>
        <h2>
          One class,<br/>three coaches,<br/><span class="red">no commitment.</span>
        </h2>
        <p class="body" style="font-size:16px;max-width:42ch;">
          Trial sessions are on the house. Bring workout gear and water — no prior
          experience needed. Jeffrey personally confirms every booking within 24&nbsp;hours.
        </p>
        <div class="contact-side">
          <div class="contact-side-row">
            <span class="label">STUDIO</span>
            <span class="val">414 Upper Paya Lebar Road, L2 Prestige Point<br/>Singapore 534994</span>
          </div>
          <div class="contact-side-row">
            <span class="label">EMAIL</span>
            <span class="val"><a href="mailto:Jeffrey.f@jfselfdefense.com">Jeffrey.f@jfselfdefense.com</a></span>
          </div>
          <div class="contact-side-row">
            <span class="label">WHATSAPP</span>
            <span class="val"><a href="https://wa.me/6596210576" target="_blank" rel="noopener">+65 9621 0576</a></span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div data-inline-trial-form></div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- FOOTER -->

</BaseLayout>
